        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 18 at 1:22PM CDT by NWS Mobile AL</headline>
        <description>At 121 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles northeast of State Line, or 9 miles west of Chatom, moving
northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Chatom and Millry.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
